div><h3>Questions about Remote Tally Access?</h3><p>Get a free 30-minute call with a Chartered Accountant, no obligation.</p><a class="gl-rotcta__btn" href="/contact-us">Book a free call &rarr;</a></div><div class="gl-rotcta__slide"><div class="gl-rotcta__badge">Talk to us</div><h3>Rather have experts handle it?</h3><p>CA-led accounting, tax and compliance for Indian businesses.</p><a class="gl-rotcta__btn" href="/contact-us">Talk to an Expert &rarr;</a></div></div><div class="gl-rotcta__dots"><span class="gl-rotcta__dot is-active" data-i="0"></span><span class="gl-rotcta__dot" data-i="1"></span><span class="gl-rotcta__dot" data-i="2"></span><span class="gl-rotcta__dot" data-i="3"></span><span class="gl-rotcta__dot" data-i="4"></span></div></aside></div></section>
  <div class="gl-tocbar"><div class="gl-wrap gl-toc"><a href="#definition" class="gl-pill is-active">Definition</a><a href="#what-is" class="gl-pill">What it is</a><a href="#how-works" class="gl-pill">How it works</a><a href="#software" class="gl-pill">In software</a><a href="#example" class="gl-pill">Example</a><a href="#mistakes" class="gl-pill">Mistakes</a><a href="#faq-section" class="gl-pill">FAQs</a></div></div>
  <div class="gl-body"><div class="gl-wrap"><div class="gl-grid"><div class="gl-main"><section id="definition" class="gl-sec"><div class="gl-eyebrow">Remote Tally Access: Definition</div><div class="definition-box"><p>Remote Tally Access is Tally&#x27;s built-in facility that lets an authorised user view and work on a company&#x27;s data from another location using a Tally.NET ID, without being on the office machine. It is enabled through the company&#x27;s online-access settings. It matters because it lets an accountant, auditor or owner reach the live books from anywhere while the data still resides on the company&#x27;s own Tally installation.</p></div></section><section id="what-is" class="gl-sec"><h2>What Is Remote Tally Access?</h2><p>Remote Tally Access uses Tally&#x27;s own Tally.NET service to connect an authorised user to a company that is running on another computer. The data stays on the host installation; the remote user logs in with a Tally.NET ID and is granted a defined level of access. It is different from screen-sharing or a VPN — it is Tally&#x27;s native remote capability, controlled by user roles set on the company itself.</p><p>An Indian business meets remote access when its accountant is not in the same room as its server. A Surat textile firm whose CA works from a different office grants the CA a Tally.NET user role and remote-access rights, so the CA can review vouchers and pull reports on the live company without a copy being emailed around. Because access is controlled centrally, it can be granted, limited or withdrawn per user at any time.</p><div class="key-terms"><p class="key-terms__title">Key terms</p><ul><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/ledger-mapping-schema">Ledger Mapping Schema</a> — The map of source ledgers to destination accounts in a migration.</li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/historical-data-cut-off-date">Historical Data Cut-off Date</a> — The date deciding how much history a project moves or reviews.</li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/erp-open-balances">ERP Open Balances</a> — The opening balances loaded when starting a new ERP.</li></ul></div></section><section id="how-works" class="gl-sec"><h2>How Remote Tally Access Works</h2><p>A remote user reaches the live company through Tally&#x27;s own service:</p><ol class="step-cards"><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">1</span><strong>Enable online access</strong><p>The company owner turns on Tally.NET services for the company — the switch that makes remote access possible.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">2</span><strong>Connect the company</strong><p>The company is connected to the Tally.NET servers, so it can be reached from outside.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">3</span><strong>Authorise the user</strong><p>A Tally.NET ID is added as a remote user with a defined role, controlling what they can see and do.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">4</span><strong>Remote user logs in</strong><p>From another location, the user opens their Tally, signs in with the Tally.NET ID and loads the company remotely.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">5</span><strong>Work within the granted role</strong><p>The remote user views reports or enters vouchers as their role permits, on the live data hosted at the office.</p></li></ol></section><section id="software" class="gl-sec"><h2>How to Set Up Remote Tally Access in Tally</h2><p>Remote access is configured from the company&#x27;s Company menu (TallyPrime centralises these under Alt+K; in Tally.ERP 9 they were split across F11 Features and Alt+F3):</p><ol class="step-cards"><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">1</span><strong>Open the Company menu</strong><p>From the Gateway of Tally, press Alt+K (Company).</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">2</span><strong>Enable Tally.NET services</strong><p>Select Online Access and set &#x27;Tally.NET Services for remote access&#x27; to Yes (optionally &#x27;Connect company on loading&#x27; to Yes), then save with Ctrl+A.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">3</span><strong>Connect the company</strong><p>From Alt+K (Company), select Connect; a (c) appears next to the company name to show it is connected.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">4</span><strong>Open Users and Passwords</strong><p>From Alt+K (Company), select Users and Passwords.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">5</span><strong>Add a Tally.NET user</strong><p>Under User Roles, pick Tally.NET User and enter the remote user&#x27;s Tally.NET ID (their email).</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">6</span><strong>Allow remote access</strong><p>Set &#x27;Allow Remote Access&#x27; to Yes for that user and save with Ctrl+A; the user can now load the company remotely with their Tally.NET ID.</p></li></ol></section><section id="example" class="gl-sec"><h2>Remote Tally Access: A Practical Example</h2><div class="gloss-table-wrap"><table class="gloss-table"><thead><tr><th>Particulars</th><th>Amount (INR)</th><th>Treatment</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Company hosted at Surat office</td><td>—</td><td>Data stays on office machine</td></tr><tr><td>CA granted Tally.NET user role</td><td>—</td><td>Remote access allowed, defined role</td></tr><tr><td>Month&#x27;s vouchers reviewed remotely</td><td>46,00,000</td><td>CA checks live data from another city</td></tr><tr><td>Report pulled remotely</td><td>—</td><td>No emailed copy of the company</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>A Surat textile firm hosts its Tally company on the office computer, while its CA works from another city. The firm enables Tally.NET services, connects the company and grants the CA a Tally.NET user role with remote access. The CA reviews the month&#x27;s ₹46,00,000 of vouchers and pulls reports on the live company remotely — no data file is emailed around, and access can be withdrawn the moment the engagement ends.</p></section><div class="gl-callout gl-callout--error"><span class="gl-callout__ic">!</span><div><div class="gl-callout__label">Common error</div><p>data permission:</p></div></div><section id="mistakes" class="gl-sec"><h2>Common Mistakes With Remote Tally Access</h2><p>Remote access needs the same care as any live-data permission:</p><ul class="gloss-bullets"><li><strong>Over-broad remote roles</strong> — Granting full rights to a remote user who only needs to view exposes the books → assign the narrowest role that fits the task.</li><li><strong>Company not connected</strong> — Enabling services but forgetting to connect the company means the remote user cannot load it → connect the company from the Company menu.</li><li><strong>Leaving access open after an engagement</strong> — Not withdrawing a remote user after work ends is a standing risk → remove or disable the Tally.NET user promptly.</li><li><strong>Host machine offline</strong> — If the hosting installation is off, remote access fails → keep the host running and connected during agreed hours.</li></ul></section><section id="related" class="gl-sec"><h2>Related Accounting Terms</h2><p>Terms around Tally access and migration:</p><ul class="related-terms"><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/ledger-mapping-schema">Ledger Mapping Schema</a> — Mapping source ledgers to destination accounts.</li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/historical-data-cut-off-date">Historical Data Cut-off Date</a> — Deciding how much history to move.</li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/erp-open-balances">ERP Open Balances</a> — Opening balances loaded into a new ERP.</li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting">Accounting Terms Glossary</a> — Browse every accounting term in one place.</li></ul></section><div class="gl-callout gl-callout--summary"><span class="gl-callout__ic">&#10003;</span><div><div class="gl-callout__label">Quick summary</div><p>Remote Tally Access is Tally&amp;#x27;s built-in facility that lets an authorised user view and work on a company&amp;#x27;s data from another location using a Tally.NET ID, without being on the office machine. It is enabled through the company&amp;#x27;s online-access settings. It matters because it lets an accountant, auditor or owner reach the live books from anywhere while the data still resides on the company&amp;#x27;s own Tally installation.</p></div></div><section class="gl-cta"><div class="gl-cta__t"><h3>Need help with Remote Tally Access?</h3><p>Remote Tally Access sits inside your day-to-day books. Patron's CA-led team keeps them accurate, compliant and audit-ready.</p></div><div class="gl-cta__btns"><a class="gl-cta__primary" href="/tally-accounting">Tally Prime Accounting Services &rarr;</a><a class="gl-cta__phone" href="tel:+919459456700">Book a consultation: +91 94594 56700</a></div></section></div><aside class="gl-aside"><div class="gl-card gl-card--service"><div class="gl-card__eyebrow">Related service</div><div class="gl-card__name">Tally Prime Accounting Services</div><p>CA-led bookkeeping, compliance and reporting for Indian businesses.</p><a class="gl-card__cta" href="/tally-accounting">Explore the service &rarr;</a></div><div class="gl-card"><div class="gl-card__eyebrow">Related services</div><ul><li><a href="/accounting-services">Accounting &amp; Bookkeeping Services in India<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li></ul></div><div class="gl-card"><div class="gl-card__eyebrow">Related terms</div><ul><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/ledger-mapping-schema">Ledger Mapping Schema<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/historical-data-cut-off-date">Historical Data Cut-off Date<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/erp-open-balances">ERP Open Balances<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting">Accounting Terms Glossary<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li></ul></div></aside></div></div></div>
  <section id="faq-section" class="gl-faq-section"><div class="faq-expanded"><aside class="faq-expanded__aside"><h2 class="faq-expanded__title">Remote Tally Access FAQs</h2><p class="faq-expanded__lead">Common questions about Remote Tally Access for Indian businesses.</p><a class="faq-expanded__cta" href="/contact-us">Still have a question? Talk to a CA &rarr;</a><form class="faq-enquiry" action="https://www.patronaccounting.com/enquiry" method="post" novalidate><h3 class="faq-enquiry__title">Talk to a CA about your books</h3><p class="faq-enquiry__sub">Share your accounting software and we'll scope the work.</p><p class="faq-enquiry__context">Enquiring about: <strong>Remote Tally Access</strong></p><input class="faq-enquiry__input" type="text" name="name" placeholder="Your name" required><input class="faq-enquiry__input" type="email" name="email" placeholder="Email" required><div class="faq-enquiry__phone"><span class="faq-enquiry__cc">+91</span><input class="faq-enquiry__input faq-enquiry__input--phone" type="tel" name="phone" placeholder="Mobile" required></div><button class="faq-enquiry__btn" type="submit">Get a Callback</button><p class="faq-enquiry__msg" role="status" aria-live="polite"></p><div class="faq-enquiry__badges"><span class="faq-enquiry__badge"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg>CA-led team</span></div></form></aside><div class="faq-expanded__list"><div class="faq-expanded__item"><h3 class="faq-expanded__q" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="faq-a1">How to enable remote access in Tally Prime?</h3><div class="faq-expanded__a" id="faq-a1"><p>Connect the company to Tally.NET in company features, create remote users against the accountant's Tally.NET identity, assign a security level, and keep the host machine and Tally running. The remote user then logs in with those credentials from another installation. An active software services subscription is required, and access can be limited to chosen vouchers and reports.</p></div></div><div class="faq-expanded__item"><h3 class="faq-expanded__q" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="faq-a2">What is the difference between Tally remote access and hosting Tally on a cloud server?</h3><div class="faq-expanded__a" id="faq-a2"><p>Remote access connects a second Tally installation to the office machine through Tally.NET, so that office computer must stay switched on and each remote user opens one company at a time. Cloud hosting places the licence and data file on a rented server that runs continuously, giving several users faster concurrent access for a monthly hosting fee.</p></div></div><div class="faq-expanded__item"><h3 class="faq-expanded__q" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="faq-a3">Can a company's books be kept on a server outside India if accessed remotely?</h3><div class="faq-expanded__a" id="faq-a3"><p>Books maintained in electronic mode must stay accessible in India at all times and a backup must be kept on servers physically located in India, with the service provider details intimated to the Registrar every year. Remote access to a file held on an Indian machine or Indian cloud satisfies this; storing data only abroad does not.</p></div></div></div></div></section>
